Please note that due to unforeseen circumstances the Post Cabinet Media Briefing scheduled for today, Thursday (13 August 2014) will no longer take place as planned.Instead, a Post Cabinet media statement outlining the outcomes of yesterday's Cabinet meeting will be issued. Apologies for any inconvenience caused.Minister in the Presidency for Planning Monitoring and Evaluation, Mr Jeff Radebe will address media on the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting held today in Cape Town. Enquiries: Phumla Williams, Acting Cabinet Spokesperson Contact: 083 501 0139 Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)